Usage:

$ python check_elasticsearch.py --help
usage: check_elasticsearch.py [-h] [-H ADDRESS] [-p INTEGER] [-w RANGE]
                              [-c RANGE] [-v] [-t TIMEOUT]
                              [CHECK]

positional arguments:
  CHECK                 Check performed (One of cluster-health, jvm-heap)

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -H ADDRESS, --hostname ADDRESS
                        Host name or IP Address (default: localhost)
  -p INTEGER, --port INTEGER
                        Port number (default: 9200)
  -w RANGE, --warning RANGE
                        warning if RESULT is outside RANGE (RESULT being
                        number of data nodes, or percent heap used)
  -c RANGE, --critical RANGE
                        critical if RESULT is outside RANGE
  -v, --verbose         increase output verbosity (use up to 3 times)
  -t TIMEOUT, --timeout TIMEOUT
                        abort execution after TIMEOUT seconds

